1
00:01:29,079 --> 00:01:30,599
The prosperity of the Southwest region

2
00:01:30,599 --> 00:01:32,480
is the envy of everyone in the land.

3
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:35,359
The Central Government has always viewed this place as a strong rear area.

4
00:01:35,719 --> 00:01:36,519
Submitting to the Central Government,

5
00:01:36,519 --> 00:01:37,239
supporting the Central Government,

6
00:01:37,239 --> 00:01:38,239
what an honor that is.

7
00:01:39,439 --> 00:01:40,920
Take a long-term view.

8
00:01:40,959 --> 00:01:43,680
Don't get hung up on immediate, petty profits.

9
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:45,079
Senator He,

10
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,680
it was Division Commander Liao under Army Commander Liu

11
00:01:47,959 --> 00:01:48,959
who played dirty first.

12
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,879
He's the villain crying victim!

13
00:01:50,959 --> 00:01:52,719
It was clearly your subordinate,

14
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:54,599
that Zhongjiang cousin, Division Commander Chen,

15
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:57,359
who seized our army's grain fields first.

16
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:58,840
We merely

17
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,120
took back the grain harvested from the fields,

18
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,560
that is all.

19
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:04,599
As long as Army Commander Liu returns the military grain to me,

20
00:02:04,599 --> 00:02:06,599
I will shake hands and make peace with him immediately.

21
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:10,480
If you return the fields and the grain in full,

22
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,959
I can still be cooperative.

23
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:13,959
What are you saying?

24
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:14,919
You want the grain,

25
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:15,759
and you want the fields too.

26
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,360
You really want the baby,

27
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:19,919
and you want the baby's mother too.

28
00:02:20,199 --> 00:02:21,479
How is that possible?

29
00:02:21,479 --> 00:02:23,120
No deal, no deal.

30
00:02:23,199 --> 00:02:24,240
So, no deal?

31
00:02:24,719 --> 00:02:25,479
No deal.

32
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,639
Then let's keep fighting.

33
00:02:27,639 --> 00:02:29,800
Let's fight! Who's afraid of whom?

34
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:30,719
You think I'm scared of you?

35
00:02:30,719 --> 00:02:32,800
I say we go outside right now and duel one-on-one!

36
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:33,840
Enough!

37
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,960
Stop playing the fool in front of me.

38
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:39,360
I solemnly tell you,

39
00:02:39,759 --> 00:02:40,719
the Central Government has specifically

40
00:02:40,719 --> 00:02:42,479
established a reserve force for this purpose

41
00:02:42,479 --> 00:02:43,879
to help you solve your problems.

42
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,919
The superiors' intention is very simple.

43
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:47,560
Either coexist peacefully

44
00:02:47,879 --> 00:02:49,000
and serve the Central Government wholeheartedly,

45
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:51,280
or the Central Government will send a garrison

46
00:02:52,599 --> 00:02:53,960
to help you coexist peacefully,

47
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,280
and teach you to serve the Central Government wholeheartedly.

48
00:03:14,719 --> 00:03:17,439
In eastern Sichuan, surrounded by mountains,

49
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:19,360
lies a town beyond the reach of the law,

50
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,560
Weiyuan.

51
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,759
In an era of rampant warlords and bandits,

52
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:27,919
the people there sang opera while eating bitter herbs,

53
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:29,719
finding joy amidst their suffering.

54
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:31,759
Especially this "Fool."

55
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,080
"Fool,"

56
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:35,560
is what Northerners call a "simpleton."

57
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,439
His foolishness was full of flavor,

58
00:03:37,599 --> 00:03:39,280
foolish enough to make you laugh and cry,

59
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:41,000
foolish to a dizzying degree,

60
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,439
foolish enough to knock you off your feet.

61
00:03:44,039 --> 00:03:46,879
He couldn't see the power struggles above,

62
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:49,319
couldn't grasp the schemes of the middle powers,

63
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:52,360
and couldn't figure out the tricks of the common folk.

64
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:56,199
He muddled through life as if it were a game.

65
00:03:57,479 --> 00:03:58,639
As the saying goes,

66
00:03:59,159 --> 00:04:00,840
"Strong winds reveal sturdy grass,"

67
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:02,879
"Turmoil produces heroes."

68
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,639
This Simpleton relied on his foolishness

69
00:04:04,759 --> 00:04:07,639
to maneuver through the chaos,

70
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:08,840
subduing demons and monsters,

71
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:11,560
finally becoming a Sichuan Army general fighting Japan,

72
00:04:11,759 --> 00:04:13,000
and living out a

73
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,960
legend in troubled times.

74
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:15,800
Oh no.

75
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,240
If I hadn't gone looking for you today,

76
00:04:20,479 --> 00:04:21,639
how would you have come back?

77
00:04:21,879 --> 00:04:23,319
You, stand still!

78
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:26,040
Did the food make you stupid?

79
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:27,920
You even poked a hornet's nest!

80
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:30,360
Look at how badly Zhang Mangzi got stung!

81
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:32,639
I hired a wet nurse at a high price,

82
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:34,439
and instead of feeding her own baby,

83
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,759
she used it all to treat his wounds.

84
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,439
Zhang Mangzi bet that I wouldn't poke the nest.

85
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:42,199
I poked it, but he was too stupid to run.

86
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:43,759
Is that my fault?

87
00:04:43,759 --> 00:04:44,319
Bet?

88
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:45,240
Bet?

89
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:46,120
Bet?

90
00:04:46,319 --> 00:04:48,279
You can't speak three sentences without betting, you!

91
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,480
Stand still!

92
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:51,759
Get down on the ground properly!

93
00:04:52,199 --> 00:04:53,199
Tell me first,

94
00:04:53,639 --> 00:04:54,399
how many hits?

95
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,279
Here it comes, here it comes.

96
00:04:55,759 --> 00:04:56,600
The thick one is coming.

97
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,639
Thick one?

98
00:05:00,639 --> 00:05:01,959
Can I even lift this?

99
00:05:02,879 --> 00:05:05,199
This cane is neither thick nor thin.

100
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,519
It's just right.

101
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,519
Do you know this cane?

102
00:05:08,879 --> 00:05:10,720
This was my father's...

103
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:12,600
your great-grandfather's.

104
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,079
Using it to beat you

105
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,959
would insult our ancestors' virtue.

106
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,519
Like planting vegetables by the outhouse,

107
00:05:18,519 --> 00:05:20,040
just make do with it.

108
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:23,959
If you don't beat me,

109
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,600
your anger won't subside.

110
00:05:28,839 --> 00:05:29,399
But if you beat me,

111
00:05:29,399 --> 00:05:31,240
you'll get tired and fall ill.

112
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,839
What will we do if you get sick?

113
00:05:33,879 --> 00:05:36,879
You're actually afraid I'll get sick?

114
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,560
Even if I'm good for nothing,

115
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,879
I still have that much filial piety.

116
00:05:42,199 --> 00:05:43,680
You have it? Some filial piety!

117
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,279
Get down on the ground!

118
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,480
Granduncle,

119
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:47,959
tell me,

120
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,040
what do I have to do

121
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,639
for you to spare me?

122
00:05:55,439 --> 00:05:56,800
The fighting is off.

123
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:58,560
I'll let you off the hook.

124
00:06:00,399 --> 00:06:01,360
Since they don't want us to fight...

125
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,639
We might as well play Mahjong.

126
00:06:02,879 --> 00:06:03,480
Red Dragon.

127
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:04,319
Regimental Commander Qin.

128
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:06,199
Your Division Commander Chen is quite something.

129
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:08,000
Sending a regimental commander to deal with us?

130
00:06:08,079 --> 00:06:10,240
Our Division Commander Chen is merely a scholar.

131
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:12,000
He doesn't know how to handle guns and cannons.

132
00:06:12,519 --> 00:06:14,720
Unlike you, Division Commander Wei.

133
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,519
You can't bear to waste a single bullet.

134
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:17,600
What did you say?

135
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:20,040
The higher-ups want us to value peace.

136
00:06:20,199 --> 00:06:22,240
So let's stop with the little tricks.

137
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:23,680
Let's go. Let's go.

138
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,199
As for this man...

139
00:06:26,199 --> 00:06:27,279
He sneaked into my military camp.

140
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,720
Asking questions left and right.

141
00:06:28,839 --> 00:06:30,000
You two...

142
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,759
Who can give me an explanation?

143
00:06:34,279 --> 00:06:35,959
Sir, it's a misunderstanding!

144
00:06:36,079 --> 00:06:37,439
I'm just a fortune teller.

145
00:06:37,519 --> 00:06:40,079
You calculated that my Chief of Staff and Brigadier Wang...

146
00:06:40,079 --> 00:06:41,519
...were astrologically incompatible with me.

147
00:06:42,319 --> 00:06:43,399
Why didn't you foresee...

148
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:45,160
...that you'd get caught by me today?

149
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,600
It really is a misunderstanding!

150
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,959
I was just telling fortunes on the street.

151
00:06:47,959 --> 00:06:49,120
An officer said my readings were accurate.

152
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,720
He insisted on dragging me into the camp...

153
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,199
...to read his superior's fortune.

154
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:54,120
Once I started, I couldn't get away.

155
00:06:54,279 --> 00:06:55,720
Every officer wanted me to read for them.

156
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:58,160
Division Commander Wei, do you know this man?

157
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,439
Never seen him.

158
00:07:02,759 --> 00:07:03,839
You don't know him either?

159
00:07:03,839 --> 00:07:04,639
I don't know him either.

160
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:05,720
Just take him out and shoot him.

161
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:06,879
Save us the trouble.

162
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,360
Sir! Spare my life! Spare me!

163
00:07:08,959 --> 00:07:10,839
I can predict many things!

164
00:07:10,839 --> 00:07:12,120
I predict...

165
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,920
The order from above to fight...

166
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,600
...is actually just an excuse...

167
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,759
...to avoid being pushed around by the top brass.

168
00:07:19,079 --> 00:07:19,959
Not necessarily.

169
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,000
One of Bamboo.

170
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:23,639
One of Bamboo. Mahjong!

171
00:07:23,639 --> 00:07:24,480
Full Flush.

172
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:25,120
Wait.

173
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,920
Two winners on one discard.

174
00:07:27,199 --> 00:07:29,160
Mixed Terminals, single wait on the One of Bamboo.

175
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:30,680
Brother Wei.

176
00:07:31,079 --> 00:07:33,560
You hit a headwind as soon as you set sail.

177
00:07:39,399 --> 00:07:41,360
The battle was called off just like that.

178
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:43,000
Otherwise...

179
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:45,199
Your butt would have been beaten to a pulp.

180
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:48,360
It means it wasn't my time to die.

181
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:53,079
Men at birth are naturally good.

182
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:56,360
Natures are similar, habits make them different.

183
00:07:56,839 --> 00:07:58,279
If not taught...

184
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,920
If not taught...

185
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,639
If not taught, nature will change.

186
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:06,199
I've recited the Three Character Classic for years.

187
00:08:06,399 --> 00:08:08,160
Don't I know that nature changes?

188
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,399
If not taught...

189
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,680
The dog doesn't bark?

190
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,399
Must have met someone it knows.

191
00:08:17,839 --> 00:08:19,279
Of course it won't bark.

192
00:08:19,279 --> 00:08:21,120
Even books written by sages have mistakes.

193
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:28,240
Boring sages hang on the wall.

194
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:31,399
Heroes and brave men roam the world.

195
00:08:33,079 --> 00:08:35,399
One day I'll walk the path of chivalry.

196
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:39,080
Helping the weak, crushing the strong, gaining fame.

197
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,200
Young Master.

198
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:42,759
The Old Master told me to supervise you.

199
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:45,559
No food if you don't study hard.

200
00:08:47,639 --> 00:08:49,919
Fan Bao, you petty villain, you jinx.

201
00:08:49,919 --> 00:08:52,000
Putting on a hat and acting all high and mighty.

202
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:52,919
I'm going off to play.

203
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,200
Young Master!

204
00:08:54,519 --> 00:08:55,399
Where are you running off to?

205
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,600
You need to study!

206
00:08:57,159 --> 00:08:57,799
Granduncle!

207
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,399
Young Master!

208
00:08:59,399 --> 00:09:00,519
Young Master, don't run!

209
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:01,720
Study, Young Master!

210
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:02,960
Young Master!

211
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,240
Where are you going?

212
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:08,039
Young Master, where are you running?

213
00:09:08,519 --> 00:09:09,960
Study! You need to study!

214
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:10,960
Young Master!

215
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:13,120
Young Master!

216
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:31,159
Young Master Fan

217
00:09:31,159 --> 00:09:31,799
Please come in, please come in

218
00:09:31,799 --> 00:09:32,600
Please come in

219
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:33,799
Please come in

220
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:34,759
Today we have

221
00:09:34,759 --> 00:09:36,159
Mengding Spring Tea and Jasmine

222
00:09:36,159 --> 00:09:38,159
Xue Tao dried tofu for a good chew

223
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,120
Look

224
00:09:39,919 --> 00:09:40,519
The usual

225
00:09:40,519 --> 00:09:41,320
Got it

226
00:09:44,919 --> 00:09:46,840
I, the Great King

227
00:09:47,759 --> 00:09:50,279
Mu Guiying

228
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,399
Hello, Mistress

229
00:09:56,519 --> 00:09:57,360
Young Master Fan

230
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,440
Hello, Mistress

231
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,320
Put it down

232
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:04,720
Move aside

233
00:10:13,639 --> 00:10:15,159
Brother Fan, are you all right?

234
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:20,320
I came specifically to visit Master Wen.

235
00:10:20,879 --> 00:10:22,200
Brother Fan, hurry up and get up.

236
00:10:24,279 --> 00:10:25,240
I can tell.

237
00:10:25,279 --> 00:10:26,720
You really do like Sichuan opera.

238
00:10:26,879 --> 00:10:28,320
Let's exchange pointers more often in the future.

239
00:10:28,399 --> 00:10:30,279
It's more than just liking it.

240
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,519
I feel that all my skills...

241
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:35,679
...were learned from listening to Master Wen's operas.

242
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:38,200
That Fahai costume you gave me...

243
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,000
...I've kept it enshrined at home.

244
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,120
I can't bear to wear it.

245
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,799
Once I've mastered the skills...

246
00:10:42,799 --> 00:10:46,519
...we'll perform "Jinshan Temple" together.

247
00:10:46,759 --> 00:10:47,519
It's a deal.

248
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,399
Worship heaven, earth, and Lord Guan.

249
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:54,320
Betray your brothers and you'll be done for.

250
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:57,360
The Brotherhood of Robbing the Rich to Feed the Poor.

251
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:01,200
The poor folks all say it's right.

252
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:05,440
You're late.

253
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:06,320
Watch it next time.

254
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,240
Okay.

255
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,600
Didn't you rob a wealthy household?

256
00:11:11,879 --> 00:11:13,559
Why is there only this little bit of flour?

257
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:14,879
Ask him.

258
00:11:15,759 --> 00:11:17,320
People call him Liang Dahu.

259
00:11:17,759 --> 00:11:19,720
Turns out his name is actually Liang Dafu.

260
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,320
I thought it meant...

261
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:22,840
...a big household with lots of grain.

262
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,279
Cut the chatter.

263
00:11:25,639 --> 00:11:26,279
How do we split this?

264
00:11:26,879 --> 00:11:28,120
I did the scouting.

265
00:11:28,559 --> 00:11:29,679
I was the lookout.

266
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,279
I did the cleanup.

267
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:33,519
I should get an extra bowl.

268
00:11:34,039 --> 00:11:34,799
I pried the door.

269
00:11:34,799 --> 00:11:35,440
I climbed the window.

270
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,320
I took the loot.

271
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,159
Then I deserve an extra bowl even more.

272
00:11:38,759 --> 00:11:40,480
You both make good points.

273
00:11:40,799 --> 00:11:41,960
So, for the sake of fairness...

274
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,000
...we'll decide by a duel.

275
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,399
Get lost.

276
00:11:44,679 --> 00:11:46,080
Not this again.

277
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,039
You take the lion's share every time.

278
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:49,440
What's the point of competing?

279
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:50,759
Who can beat you anyway?

280
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:52,360
I want to join in too.

281
00:11:53,679 --> 00:11:54,840
Young Master Fan.

282
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,519
You have a wealthy family and a big business.

283
00:11:56,679 --> 00:11:57,519
Why do you want to fight for food...

284
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:59,440
...with us folks who live hand to mouth?

285
00:11:59,759 --> 00:12:02,919
Eldest Brother leads us in the jianghu...

286
00:12:02,919 --> 00:12:04,840
...to uphold justice and chivalry.

287
00:12:05,279 --> 00:12:06,639
He set a rule long ago.

288
00:12:07,039 --> 00:12:08,320
For every job we pull...

289
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,240
...we must help a poor person.

290
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:11,960
Today, I represent...

291
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:13,519
Granny Wang.

292
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:14,840
Well said.

293
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,559
We can't forget the rules.

294
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,039
When roaming the jianghu...

295
00:12:18,159 --> 00:12:19,279
...what is most important?

296
00:12:19,399 --> 00:12:20,759
Honor.

297
00:12:22,519 --> 00:12:24,080
Honor is the most important thing.

298
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,679
Your grandnephew...

299
00:12:25,679 --> 00:12:27,240
...is thirty-seven or thirty-eight.

300
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:31,399
That's his nominal age, nominal age.

301
00:12:31,639 --> 00:12:33,159
He is the sole heir of the family.

302
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:36,159
You want him to focus on his studies...

303
00:12:36,679 --> 00:12:38,480
...but who knew that Young Master Fan...

304
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:39,480
...is a bit too fond of playing?

305
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:41,799
He causes trouble from morning till night.

306
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:44,279
Find me someone fierce.

307
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:48,320
Rumor has it that the Young Master has a "hard fate."

308
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:49,639
His parents at home...

309
00:12:49,639 --> 00:12:51,279
...were all cursed to death by him.

310
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,440
I've introduced seven or eight girls to him...

311
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:58,200
...but none of them worked out.

312
00:12:58,279 --> 00:12:59,600
Then find someone even fiercer.

313
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:04,279
I, Matchmaker Tian...

314
00:13:04,279 --> 00:13:06,360
...am quite famous in this town.

315
00:13:06,759 --> 00:13:08,519
If you think there's no way...

316
00:13:08,519 --> 00:13:09,960
...that's not entirely true.

317
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,440
It's just that...

318
00:13:12,679 --> 00:13:14,320
Find me someone who can control him.

319
00:13:16,039 --> 00:13:18,399
I just thought of the perfect person.

320
00:13:18,799 --> 00:13:20,240
I'll go talk to them right away.

321
00:13:37,559 --> 00:13:39,000
You're pretty good.

322
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,080
You son of a turtle.

323
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:50,639
Come on then.

324
00:13:52,919 --> 00:13:53,720
What happened?

325
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:56,600
I practiced exactly according to

326
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:59,440
the book you sold me, didn't I?

327
00:13:59,679 --> 00:14:00,679
So where exactly

328
00:14:00,879 --> 00:14:01,879
did I lose?

329
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:03,679
This *True Spirit Sutra*...

330
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:05,960
the most important thing is the "Spirit".

331
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,519
There are spirits in the heavens,

332
00:14:07,679 --> 00:14:08,559
spirits in the earth,

333
00:14:08,759 --> 00:14:10,039
and spirits among men.

334
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,879
As for the spirits among men,

335
00:14:12,919 --> 00:14:14,480
it depends on you,

336
00:14:14,679 --> 00:14:16,320
what kind of "spirit" you can realize.

337
00:14:17,919 --> 00:14:18,759
A born fool.

338
00:15:07,039 --> 00:15:09,519
Young Master, Young Master, Young Master!

339
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:10,799
It's terrible!

340
00:15:10,799 --> 00:15:12,039
Something big has happened!

341
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,240
Granduncle!

342
00:15:15,639 --> 00:15:18,399
I won't go through with this marriage!

343
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:23,360
I'd rather die than marry!

344
00:15:25,159 --> 00:15:26,639
Why aren't you hitting me?

345
00:15:27,519 --> 00:15:28,480
Young Master,

346
00:15:28,759 --> 00:15:30,360
you've been dry-wailing for so long,

347
00:15:30,759 --> 00:15:32,399
but you haven't wailed the Old Master out here.

348
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:35,279
If you don't hit me, how can I wail?

349
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:36,399
Hit me.

350
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:50,240
You're more ruthless than Granduncle.

351
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,559
You told me to hit hard!

352
00:15:53,159 --> 00:15:54,799
Hitting me like this,

353
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:57,320
I might as well ask Granduncle to hit me.

354
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,519
Then ask him to come hit you.

355
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:00,320
But he won't come out.

356
00:16:00,679 --> 00:16:01,279
Go find him then.

357
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:03,519
Young Master,

358
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:04,879
if you hit me

359
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:06,960
and it means you don't have to marry,

360
00:16:07,639 --> 00:16:08,559
then hit hard.

361
00:16:13,919 --> 00:16:16,679
You can't escape what's coming.

362
00:16:17,039 --> 00:16:17,720
Let's go.

363
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:32,799
Granduncle.

364
00:16:34,159 --> 00:16:34,960
I know.

365
00:16:35,799 --> 00:16:37,159
You want me to come here

366
00:16:37,159 --> 00:16:38,639
and admit my mistake to the ancestors.

367
00:16:39,879 --> 00:16:40,639
Fan Bao.

368
00:16:41,279 --> 00:16:43,000
In front of the ancestors,

369
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:44,600
hit me hard.

370
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:46,159
After the beating,

371
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:48,399
I won't have to go through with this marriage.

372
00:16:48,639 --> 00:16:49,600
Hit me!

373
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,159
Enough.

374
00:16:53,919 --> 00:16:55,240
Enough!

375
00:16:55,519 --> 00:16:57,200
Stop the charade.

376
00:16:57,759 --> 00:16:59,000
This marriage,

377
00:16:59,679 --> 00:17:00,799
is set in stone.

378
00:17:01,159 --> 00:17:02,120
Granduncle, I...

379
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,399
I really know I was wrong.

380
00:17:03,399 --> 00:17:04,519
Really.

381
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:07,360
I promise the ancestors,

382
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:09,840
I won't go out and cause trouble anymore.

383
00:17:09,919 --> 00:17:11,400
Forcing me to marry

384
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:14,519
is driving me to my death!

385
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:23,440
Either you get married,

386
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:27,000
or I'll lie in there right now.

387
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:36,599
Boss Liu, congratulations!

388
00:17:36,599 --> 00:17:37,400
Congratulations.

389
00:17:37,799 --> 00:17:40,119
Elder Wang, Elder Wang.

390
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:43,000
An auspicious cloud blooms in the east,

391
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:45,960
a purple cloud arrives from the west.

392
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:49,599
Auspicious and purple clouds meet,

393
00:17:50,119 --> 00:17:55,400
the bride and groom come to bow.

394
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:00,480
First bow to Heaven and Earth!

395
00:18:00,799 --> 00:18:02,279
Bow to Heaven and Earth!

396
00:18:11,079 --> 00:18:12,839
Second bow to Granduncle!

397
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,599
Bow to Granduncle!

398
00:18:19,519 --> 00:18:21,359
Husband and wife bow to each other!

399
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:28,200
Enter the bridal chamber!

400
00:18:34,799 --> 00:18:35,960
What do I do?

401
00:18:36,519 --> 00:18:38,200
I can't take your place.

402
00:18:38,799 --> 00:18:41,480
Granduncle! Granduncle!

403
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,720
If you want to tie me down,

404
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:46,319
find a better rope!

405
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,720
I'm clearly a Golden Arhat,

406
00:18:48,759 --> 00:18:51,599
but you insist on matching me with patched-up clothes!

407
00:18:53,119 --> 00:18:54,480
I'm going to study!

408
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:56,680
There's no escaping this.

409
00:19:00,799 --> 00:19:02,680
I'll go in and call her Grandma,

410
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,200
and let her live with Granduncle!

411
00:19:15,279 --> 00:19:16,160
Let me tell you something

412
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:17,880
I don't have any money

413
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,599
The money all belongs to Granduncle

414
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,519
Why don't you marry Granduncle?

415
00:19:21,920 --> 00:19:23,039
Our Granduncle...

416
00:19:23,359 --> 00:19:25,200
...has been single for decades

417
00:19:25,759 --> 00:19:27,599
Like aged wine, he's pure essence

418
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,240
Plenty of middle-aged ladies have their eyes on him

419
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,000
You wouldn't be losing out

420
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:36,599
You really are a Simpleton

421
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:37,599
I may be silly...

422
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:39,480
...but Granduncle isn't

423
00:19:40,359 --> 00:19:42,160
Stop talking nonsense

424
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:10,240
Good heavens!

425
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:13,400
I thought you were... that person

426
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,720
Who is "that person"?

427
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,839
I have a name. It's Yu Zhen

428
00:20:18,599 --> 00:20:19,759
You should call me Grandma

429
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:22,000
I'm not that stupid

430
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:27,640
I have a tough fate

431
00:20:28,039 --> 00:20:28,920
Aren't you afraid?

432
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:29,519
No

433
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:31,200
I'm even harder than you

434
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:33,240
I'm here to discipline you on Granduncle's behalf

435
00:20:38,119 --> 00:20:40,160
I'm willing to let you handle me

436
00:20:42,359 --> 00:20:43,519
Didn't you say...

437
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,079
...you wanted to study?

438
00:20:46,119 --> 00:20:47,039
I am studying

439
00:20:49,119 --> 00:20:49,720
Today...

440
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:52,240
...I'm going to study the book of "you"

441
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,240
In broad daylight?

442
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:54,720
People outside can see us

443
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:56,240
What's there to be afraid of?

444
00:20:56,359 --> 00:20:57,839
We're legally married

445
00:20:57,839 --> 00:20:59,039
Who cares?

446
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:04,000
I've stumbled right into paradise

447
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:06,400
Just my dumb luck

448
00:21:08,039 --> 00:21:10,039
My father was a schoolteacher

449
00:21:10,039 --> 00:21:10,920
He passed away early

450
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:12,920
I used to have an older brother

451
00:21:13,279 --> 00:21:14,759
He also fell ill and died

452
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:17,400
Leaving just my mother and me to rely on each other

453
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:20,839
She just wanted me to marry into a good family

454
00:21:21,519 --> 00:21:23,319
I really thank your mother

455
00:21:28,799 --> 00:21:30,440
Just as I'm getting emotional, you son of a...

456
00:21:32,839 --> 00:21:34,039
Come and catch me!

457
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:36,400
Come and catch me!

458
00:21:46,519 --> 00:21:47,519
Where did this stray cat come from?

459
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:48,839
Is it in heat?

460
00:21:58,039 --> 00:22:01,000
Zhongjiang black pork with garlic sauce

461
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:02,039
Here

462
00:22:05,799 --> 00:22:07,039
You're quite the cook

463
00:22:30,319 --> 00:22:31,119
Wait a moment

464
00:22:31,279 --> 00:22:32,839
You still need to wash your face

465
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:41,559
You really are a Simpleton

466
00:22:44,359 --> 00:22:45,200
Yu Zhen

467
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:47,519
I've got it all nice and warm

468
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,119
Come up here, quick

469
00:22:58,039 --> 00:22:58,839
Is it warm?

470
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:00,960
It can get even warmer

471
00:23:02,799 --> 00:23:05,640
Guidelines for Students, the Sages' teachings

472
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:08,480
Guidelines for Students, the Sages' teachings

473
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,640
First be filial, next be trustworthy

474
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:15,440
First be filial, next be trustworthy

475
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:18,839
Love everyone, draw near to virtue

476
00:23:19,119 --> 00:23:21,799
Love everyone, draw near to virtue

477
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:26,400
If energy remains, then study the arts

478
00:23:26,599 --> 00:23:29,359
If energy remains, then study the arts

479
00:23:31,559 --> 00:23:33,119
Study hard now

480
00:23:33,359 --> 00:23:34,160
Alright

481
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,440
Let me tell you...

482
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:36,640
...you have to memorize it

483
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:37,440
You got it

484
00:23:48,599 --> 00:23:51,880
Finally, I am worthy of the Fan family's

485
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:54,359
ancestors.

486
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,279
Division Commander Liao,

487
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:58,480
I really am a fortune teller!

488
00:24:03,279 --> 00:24:04,960
Well, uh, well...

489
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:06,480
Right now, Sichuan is divided into three factions.

490
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:08,200
Those capable of assisting a wise ruler,

491
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:09,759
like the Sleeping Dragon and Phoenix, are rare.

492
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,119
I can help you find a lucky general

493
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,480
who can strategize and execute grand plans.

494
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:16,559
You?

495
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:17,240
No, no, no.

496
00:24:17,319 --> 00:24:18,799
I've been observing the stars these past few nights.

497
00:24:18,799 --> 00:24:20,920
I discovered a lucky general not seen in a century.

498
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:22,559
He is the incarnation of the Wisdom Star.

499
00:24:22,559 --> 00:24:23,559
Skilled in both literary and martial arts.

500
00:24:23,559 --> 00:24:24,640
Brave and resourceful.

501
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:26,960
It's a pity he's still lost among the common folk.

502
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,480
He is currently undergoing eighty-one tribulations.

503
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:29,880
Is he a monkey?

504
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:31,680
He was actually born in the Year of the Monkey.

505
00:24:32,319 --> 00:24:33,759
Commander, Commander, Commander!

506
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,400
You are a hero of these chaotic times.

507
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,680
If you wish to achieve supremacy,

508
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:38,200
you must have a lucky general to assist you.

509
00:24:40,119 --> 00:24:40,920
Fine.

510
00:24:41,519 --> 00:24:42,839
I will trust you this one time.

511
00:24:43,039 --> 00:24:44,680
Finding someone takes time and effort.

512
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:47,000
I'm afraid one can't make bricks without straw.

513
00:24:47,039 --> 00:24:47,920
What do you mean?

514
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:49,799
Could you...

515
00:24:49,960 --> 00:24:51,359
give me a deposit?

516
00:24:51,559 --> 00:24:53,079
Your life is the deposit.

517
00:25:07,079 --> 00:25:07,960
I'm off then!

518
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,359
Since you've been behaving yourself lately,

519
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,359
Granduncle has asked you to go collect debts.

520
00:25:15,599 --> 00:25:16,720
It wasn't easy for the old man

521
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:17,680
to lift your grounding.

522
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:19,839
Make sure you don't cause any more trouble.

523
00:25:20,079 --> 00:25:20,880
Got it.

524
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,359
Where are you going?

525
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:36,759
Young Master Fan, ever since you got married,

526
00:25:37,359 --> 00:25:38,720
you haven't stepped out the door once.

527
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:41,559
Doesn't he miss his brothers?

528
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:44,319
Damn men, after they get married,

529
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:46,440
are they all like this?

530
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:47,599
You wouldn't understand.

531
00:25:48,519 --> 00:25:49,359
Brother Fan!

532
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:50,480
Young Master Fan!

533
00:25:50,599 --> 00:25:51,400
Brother Fan!

534
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:52,559
What are you guys doing here?

535
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:54,759
We've finally waited you out.

536
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:57,240
Oh no.

537
00:25:58,480 --> 00:25:59,440
What's the matter?

538
00:26:05,119 --> 00:26:06,279
Yu Zhen!

539
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:08,000
Yu Zhen!

540
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:13,400
I forgot to tell you something important!

541
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:14,440
What is it?

542
00:26:14,720 --> 00:26:16,880
That boil on your butt...

543
00:26:17,039 --> 00:26:18,599
make sure you remember to apply the ointment.

544
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:20,640
And don't sit on any hard benches!

545
00:26:21,799 --> 00:26:22,960
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

546
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:24,400
You have to walk the road with your feet.

547
00:26:24,519 --> 00:26:25,920
You know how to do that, right?

548
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:27,880
Hurry up and go.

549
00:26:32,480 --> 00:26:33,440
Simpleton!

550
00:26:33,799 --> 00:26:34,720
Come back!

551
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:36,200
I'm back.

552
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,519
Say whatever you have to say all at once,

553
00:26:39,319 --> 00:26:41,319
so you don't have to run back all sweaty.

554
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:43,400
That's it, that's it.

555
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:45,599
Hurry back.

556
00:26:47,519 --> 00:26:48,319
I'm off!

557
00:26:53,839 --> 00:26:54,359
Coming!

558
00:26:54,359 --> 00:26:55,200
Coming, coming!

559
00:27:03,680 --> 00:27:04,799
In this vast world,

560
00:27:05,119 --> 00:27:06,480
isn't brotherhood the greatest?

561
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:12,279
Yes!

562
00:27:12,319 --> 00:27:13,119
The mountains are high,

563
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:14,039
the waters are deep,

564
00:27:14,279 --> 00:27:15,880
but isn't brotherhood the deepest?

565
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:17,359
Yes!

566
00:27:17,480 --> 00:27:18,559
Your brother's life or death—

567
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:20,920
do you still care about it?

568
00:27:21,039 --> 00:27:23,920
People of the Jianghu never flake out!

569
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:34,559
You sure are living it up.

570
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:37,319
While us brothers are starving to death.

571
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:39,799
So hungry I'm tripping over my own feet.

572
00:27:40,319 --> 00:27:41,519
Falling flat on my face.

573
00:27:42,759 --> 00:27:44,640
I'm like a monk's head, too.

574
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:46,279
I've got no way out.

575
00:27:47,920 --> 00:27:49,799
Once I collect the debts...

576
00:27:50,119 --> 00:27:51,119
We'll discuss it then.

577
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:52,519
Collecting debts?

578
00:27:52,839 --> 00:27:53,920
Why didn't you say you were collecting debts?

579
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:55,319
You should've asked the brothers to back you up!

580
00:27:56,119 --> 00:27:57,519
Even if it's a mountain of blades or a sea of fire...

581
00:27:57,519 --> 00:27:58,960
We brothers will go with you.

582
00:27:58,960 --> 00:27:59,920
Let's go, together. Let's go.

583
00:28:01,079 --> 00:28:03,039
Piping hot mutton soup!

584
00:28:03,039 --> 00:28:04,559
Come and get it!

585
00:28:06,119 --> 00:28:08,839
Authentic Weiyuan mutton soup!

586
00:28:08,839 --> 00:28:09,680
Boss.

587
00:28:10,039 --> 00:28:12,480
I'm here to collect the rent for these past few months.

588
00:28:13,279 --> 00:28:13,920
You want more soup?

589
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:14,559
Coming right up!

590
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:16,799
Coming, coming, coming!

591
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:18,079
Here you go.

592
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:19,559
Fill it up, fill it up!

593
00:28:19,839 --> 00:28:21,200
Here, here, here.

594
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:21,960
What the heck are you doing?

595
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,000
It's brim-full already!

596
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:25,799
It doesn't cost anything, honestly.

597
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:26,880
Pay the rent.

598
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:28,400
The bill?

599
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:30,720
Coming, coming, coming!

600
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:31,559
Stand still!

601
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:34,440
Are you paying or not?

602
00:28:34,799 --> 00:28:35,839
Young Master Fan.

603
00:28:35,839 --> 00:28:37,559
You can see I'm busy right now.

604
00:28:37,599 --> 00:28:38,640
It's not like I won't pay you.

605
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:39,839
Just come back another day.

606
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:40,720
If you don't pay today...

607
00:28:41,359 --> 00:28:43,319
It'll be like threshing grain in the rain.

608
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:44,960
It won't end well.

609
00:28:45,599 --> 00:28:46,440
What are you doing?

610
00:28:47,480 --> 00:28:48,599
You want to hit me?

611
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:49,599
Let me tell you.

612
00:28:49,720 --> 00:28:51,839
They call me "One Touch Fall" around here.

613
00:28:52,039 --> 00:28:54,279
If you knock me over...

614
00:28:54,319 --> 00:28:55,839
Not only will you not get the rent...

615
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:56,960
My three wives...

616
00:28:56,960 --> 00:28:57,720
And eight kids...

617
00:28:57,880 --> 00:28:58,640
You'll have to support them all.

618
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:02,519
Here we come, here we come!

619
00:29:03,519 --> 00:29:03,960
Let's go.

620
00:29:05,759 --> 00:29:06,599
Go, go, go.

621
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:07,279
Stop eating!

622
00:29:08,400 --> 00:29:09,480
That mutton soup...

623
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:10,880
It only tastes good with some wine added.

624
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:11,759
Come on, come on.

625
00:29:12,319 --> 00:29:13,119
Pay up.

626
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:14,599
Does it taste good?

627
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:15,559
Let me have a sip.

628
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:17,039
Boss, do something!

629
00:29:18,039 --> 00:29:19,039
Do what? I can't do anything!

630
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:20,279
The boss is treating everyone today!

631
00:29:20,279 --> 00:29:21,279
Go, go, go!

632
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:21,920
No need to pay!

633
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:23,519
No, no!

634
00:29:24,599 --> 00:29:25,960
You guys are wrecking my business!

635
00:29:26,319 --> 00:29:27,119
I'm going to report you to the authorities!

636
00:29:27,240 --> 00:29:28,400
Go ahead and report it!

637
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,039
I'll sue you right back...

638
00:29:30,119 --> 00:29:31,039
For owing money and not paying!

639
00:29:31,599 --> 00:29:32,279
Let's go!

640
00:29:32,359 --> 00:29:33,440
It's even livelier inside!

641
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:34,000
Go, go, go!

642
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:34,920
You can't, you can't!

643
00:29:36,079 --> 00:29:38,319
I'll pay, I'll pay!

644
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:41,400
See?

645
00:29:41,599 --> 00:29:42,720
When the brothers step in...

646
00:29:42,799 --> 00:29:43,880
Instant success.

647
00:29:44,319 --> 00:29:45,160
So, what do you say?

648
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:46,960
You should treat everyone to a meat meal.

649
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:48,519
This...

650
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:50,920
I have to hand this over to Granduncle.

651
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:52,599
I need to make a good impression.

652
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:54,759
Your wife has only been here a few days...

653
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:56,279
And you've already forgotten our brotherhood?

654
00:29:56,319 --> 00:29:56,920
Exactly!

655
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:57,400
Heartbreaking.

656
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:58,039
My heart aches.

657
00:29:58,039 --> 00:29:59,519
It hurts deep down in my soul.

658
00:30:00,039 --> 00:30:00,720
You've changed.

659
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:02,480
You're no longer the...

660
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:04,000
Righteous and loyal Young Master Fan.

661
00:30:04,680 --> 00:30:06,359
Saying that about Young Master Fan...

662
00:30:06,359 --> 00:30:08,279
Is like weighing manure in the toilet.

663
00:30:08,319 --> 00:30:09,240
That's too much!

664
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:12,400
But the brothers helped you with all their hearts.

665
00:30:12,759 --> 00:30:13,680
Giving a little kickback...

666
00:30:14,119 --> 00:30:14,920
Isn't too much to ask, is it?

667
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:17,720
How much do you want?

668
00:30:34,319 --> 00:30:35,640
Let's go. Next one.

669
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:36,519
Let's go.

670
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:38,480
How much is it exactly?

671
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:39,720
I'm not telling you.

672
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:41,359
Young Master Fan.

673
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:42,480
Whatever catches your eye here...

674
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:43,519
Just take whatever you want.

675
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:45,240
If you want me to pay rent...

676
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:46,640
I can't cough up the cash.

677
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:48,440
What do you mean you can't cough it up?

678
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:51,640
How about this?

679
00:30:51,839 --> 00:30:53,519
I'll forge you a handy weapon...

680
00:30:53,759 --> 00:30:54,759
To cover the rent.

681
00:30:58,039 --> 00:30:58,839
You just...

682
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:01,240
Make me something I want to pay off the debt.

683
00:31:01,799 --> 00:31:02,519
What is it?

684
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:06,680
This.

685
00:31:06,960 --> 00:31:09,200
Is exactly what I want most.

686
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:10,799
What's the use of this?

687
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:12,440
None of your damn business.

688
00:31:17,319 --> 00:31:18,160
Pay up.

689
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:20,200
Young Master Fan.

690
00:31:20,799 --> 00:31:22,960
Business has been terrible.

691
00:31:23,319 --> 00:31:24,640
I really can't afford the rent.

692
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:26,839
So what do we do?

693
00:31:27,359 --> 00:31:27,880
How about...

694
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:29,519
I give you my son as payment?

695
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:30,559
As a bodyguard...

696
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:31,480
Or to carry your bags.

697
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:32,640
He can do anything.

698
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:35,039
You're giving me this beanpole?

699
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:36,480
If it were a woman...

700
00:31:36,759 --> 00:31:37,880
We might consider it.

701
00:31:38,759 --> 00:31:39,880
Look at him.

702
00:31:40,039 --> 00:31:41,079
What can he actually do?

703
00:31:46,319 --> 00:31:47,119
Dad, watch this.

704
00:31:58,160 --> 00:32:00,480
That's actually pretty impressive.

705
00:32:01,079 --> 00:32:03,240
He's good enough to tag along for a meal.

706
00:32:03,759 --> 00:32:05,400
Another mouth to feed?

707
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:07,240
Just look at him.

708
00:32:07,359 --> 00:32:09,200
A dried shrimp like him won't eat much.

709
00:32:09,440 --> 00:32:10,160
Hurry up!

710
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:11,200
Thank you, Young Master Fan!

711
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:13,519
Thank you, Young Master Fan!

712
00:32:15,079 --> 00:32:16,160
Perform a special skill...

713
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:17,680
And you can pay off the rent.

714
00:32:36,119 --> 00:32:36,920
This is great.

715
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:57,960
I used to be the baby of the group.

716
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:59,559
Now that a new brother has joined...

717
00:32:59,559 --> 00:33:00,640
I'm still the baby.

718
00:33:00,960 --> 00:33:01,960
I'm not having it.

719
00:33:02,519 --> 00:33:04,079
Emperors love the eldest son.

720
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:05,519
Commoners love the youngest son.

721
00:33:06,359 --> 00:33:07,960
Debt collecting turned into scrap collecting.

722
00:33:08,119 --> 00:33:09,240
Only you could pull that off.

723
00:33:10,519 --> 00:33:12,839
They really couldn't pay up.

724
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:14,359
The cut for the brothers...

725
00:33:14,359 --> 00:33:16,359
Is less than the fat on a chicken leg.

726
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:17,720
We probably need a raise.

727
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:20,640
Yeah, two more mouths to feed.

728
00:33:21,519 --> 00:33:23,240
The brothers have risked their lives for you.

729
00:33:23,920 --> 00:33:25,319
You value loyalty the most.

730
00:33:25,759 --> 00:33:27,160
You gotta give us a raise.

731
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:30,119
I'll take you to the opera.

732
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:31,960
To satisfy your craving.

733
00:33:32,319 --> 00:33:35,160
Our Master Wen's "Guiying Hunting Geese"...

734
00:33:35,480 --> 00:33:37,160
He sings it beautifully.

735
00:33:52,279 --> 00:33:53,640
Why isn't the show on?

736
00:33:55,640 --> 00:33:57,119
Paying back debts

737
00:33:57,119 --> 00:33:58,559
is the law of nature.

738
00:34:00,319 --> 00:34:02,200
I've been here so many damn times.

739
00:34:02,319 --> 00:34:04,279
You really won't show Scarface any respect?

740
00:34:05,359 --> 00:34:05,960
Sir.

741
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,640
My husband is so sick.

742
00:34:07,640 --> 00:34:08,920
Let's talk outside.

743
00:34:15,159 --> 00:34:16,760
Our family really has no money left.

744
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:18,840
All the money went to treating his illness.

745
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:20,840
Just give me two more days of grace.

746
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:22,760
My money comes from three knives and six holes,

747
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:24,639
dug out of a basin of blood.

748
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:25,679
If you don't pay,

749
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:27,360
I can't report back to my boss either.

750
00:34:27,559 --> 00:34:28,760
What's going on? What's going on?

751
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:30,719
What a racket.

752
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:32,079
Master Wen, come here.

753
00:34:32,559 --> 00:34:33,679
Collecting debts owed.

754
00:34:33,760 --> 00:34:34,760
Mind your own business and crawl away.

755
00:34:34,920 --> 00:34:36,159
Only turtles crawl.

756
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:37,760
Why don't you crawl for me to see?

757
00:34:38,039 --> 00:34:39,760
Whose belt wasn't tied tight,

758
00:34:39,760 --> 00:34:41,519
that let you bastards loose?

759
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:42,559
Asking for a beating.

760
00:34:42,639 --> 00:34:43,599
Who are you?

761
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:45,360
It's spacious outside. Come on.

762
00:34:45,679 --> 00:34:46,320
Let's go.

763
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:47,519
Come on, come on, let's go.

764
00:34:47,719 --> 00:34:48,199
Move.

765
00:34:48,559 --> 00:34:49,480
Who's afraid of whom?

766
00:34:49,599 --> 00:34:50,360
Come on then.

767
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:51,440
Stay here.

768
00:34:56,760 --> 00:34:58,960
I think you're swatting flies on a tiger's head.

769
00:34:59,119 --> 00:35:00,400
Tired of living.

770
00:35:00,519 --> 00:35:02,039
Drawing a circle on two sheets of paper...

771
00:35:02,039 --> 00:35:02,880
You have such a big face.

772
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,440
With a little topknot on your head,

773
00:35:04,679 --> 00:35:05,840
you think you're taller than me?

774
00:35:06,159 --> 00:35:07,840
You're a worm fighting a rooster.

775
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:08,679
You're looking to die.

776
00:35:08,679 --> 00:35:09,199
Come on.

777
00:35:09,239 --> 00:35:09,639
Come on.

778
00:35:09,719 --> 00:35:10,199
Come on.

779
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:10,800
Bring it on.

780
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:14,360
I don't have time to waste with you.

781
00:35:15,079 --> 00:35:15,920
Scram.
